

Functions and Keywords:
- Building blocks of syntax.
- Functions - pieces of code - perform a unit of work.
    Python Built-in functions - https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html
- Keywords - Reserved words - to construct instructions.
    Examples - https://www.programiz.com/python-programming/keyword-list


Data Types Recap:
- String - text in between quotes - single or double
- Integer - Whole Number - without fraction
- Float - Real Number - with fraction

- Mixing incompatible data types - may encounter a TypeError.
- Check the data type - using type() function.


Type Conversion:
- Convert variable from one data type to another
- Implicit Conversion - interpreter automatically converts
- Explicit Conversion - Manually convert by calling a function eg. str()

eg.
total = 2048 + 4375 + 97685 + 125 + 8
files = 5
average = total / files
print("Average file siez is " + str(average))


Defining Functions:
- Start with 'def' keyword - followed by function name + parameters - end in ':'
- Followed by consistently indented function body.
- Optional 'return' at the end - multiple values can be returned
- If no return values mentioned - function returns 'None'


Code Style
- Critical for readability of code.
- Extensively use comments - improve readability.
- Use relevant names for variables and function names.


